python-scipy
------------------------------------------
SciPy is a collection of mathematical algorithms and convenience 
functions built on the Numpy extension for Python. It adds significant 
power to the interactive Python session by exposing the user to 
high-level commands and classes for the manipulation and visualization 
of data. With SciPy, an interactive Python session becomes a 
data-processing and system-prototyping environment rivaling sytems such 
as Matlab, IDL, Octave, R-Lab, and SciLab.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-60
  libarpack0-96-1
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2
  libgfortran3-4.3.2-2
  liblapack0-3.1.1-2
  libstdc++6-4.3.2-2
  python-2.5.4-10
  python-numpy-1.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  gcc4-g++-4.3.2-2
  gcc4-fortran-4.3.2-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.scipy.org/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/scipy/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack python-scipy-0.7.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./python-scipy-0.7.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/python-scipy-0.7.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/python-scipy-0.7.1-X.tar.bz2

A list of the files in the binary package is available from the
command-line with "cygcheck -l python-scipy", or online at
<http://cygwin.com/packages/python-scipy/>.

-------------------------------------------

